SIMPLE: semi-arian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semi-Arian
<hw>Sem`i-A"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Arian</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>A member of a
branch of the Arians which did not acknowledge the Son to be
consubstantial with the Father, that is, of the same substance, but
admitted him to be of a like substance with the Father, not by nature,
but by a peculiar privilege.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semi-Arian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Semi-Arian
<hw>Sem"i-A"ri*an</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
Semi-Arianism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semi-Arianism</ent>⟦br⟧
